1
00:00:01,023 --> 00:00:02,033
Hello.

2
00:00:02,033 --> 00:00:03,293
(Samun TV)

3
00:00:03,293 --> 00:00:05,763
My name is Ko Seong Hui.

4
00:00:06,403 --> 00:00:09,233
I am the wife of Chairman Park Jin Seok...

5
00:00:09,973 --> 00:00:11,103
of the Shoe Joy Group.

6
00:00:20,383 --> 00:00:23,413
She entered Unit 709 in the Sky Castle complex.

7
00:00:24,453 --> 00:00:25,553
Why would she go in there?

8
00:00:32,393 --> 00:00:35,163
- Yes, Chairman. - Mr. Park, what is this?

9
00:00:36,493 --> 00:00:38,803
Is this it? Just a photo of the door to 709?

10
00:00:39,363 --> 00:00:41,733
She made no attempt to avoid us.

11
00:00:42,003 --> 00:00:44,103
She even asked us to go up in the elevator with her,

12
00:00:44,173 --> 00:00:46,043
so I couldn't bring myself to take a picture of her going in.

13
00:00:47,243 --> 00:00:48,513
She asked you to go up with her?

14
00:00:52,413 --> 00:00:55,583
I never gave you permission to put a lien on my properties,

15
00:00:56,313 --> 00:00:58,653
and I never authorized you to use my official seal.

16
00:00:59,953 --> 00:01:00,953
And...

17
00:01:02,993 --> 00:01:04,093
I'm sorry...

18
00:01:04,893 --> 00:01:06,023
that it's come to this.

19
00:01:14,203 --> 00:01:15,333
To all subscribers,

20
00:01:16,703 --> 00:01:18,103
thank you for hearing me out.

21
00:01:18,173 --> 00:01:20,073
(Samun TV)

22
00:01:20,143 --> 00:01:21,713
Once this video is released,

23
00:01:22,443 --> 00:01:24,273
I don't know what will happen to me.

24
00:01:26,613 --> 00:01:27,683
I hope all of you...

25
00:01:29,083 --> 00:01:30,653
will continue to follow my story.

26
00:01:42,163 --> 00:01:44,193
(Samun TV)

27
00:01:45,103 --> 00:01:46,233
All done?

28
00:01:49,803 --> 00:01:51,673
You spoke very well.

29
00:01:55,243 --> 00:01:57,043
Please upload this tomorrow at 10am.

30
00:01:57,543 --> 00:01:59,243
Yes, at 10am sharp.

31
00:02:00,313 --> 00:02:01,413
Tonight,

32
00:02:02,583 --> 00:02:03,813
I'd like to get a good night's sleep.

33
00:02:13,393 --> 00:02:16,633
It's Ji Eun Oh, isn't it? Your long-time crush.

34
00:02:18,303 --> 00:02:19,363
You girls...

35
00:02:20,103 --> 00:02:21,403
How are you always so quick to catch on?

36
00:02:23,903 --> 00:02:25,443
You'll never get over her...

37
00:02:25,803 --> 00:02:27,543
if you keep running into her like this.

38
00:02:32,443 --> 00:02:33,743
What is it you want me to say?

39
00:02:34,583 --> 00:02:36,313
You could fall for her again at any moment.

40
00:02:36,683 --> 00:02:37,983
Must be nice for you.

41
00:02:41,383 --> 00:02:42,793
She's the girl Ji Hyuk likes.

42
00:02:44,963 --> 00:02:45,963
What?

43
00:02:46,563 --> 00:02:47,693
And Eun Oh...

44
00:02:48,563 --> 00:02:49,793
likes Ji Hyuk, too.

45
00:02:51,463 --> 00:02:53,633
- Really? - But...

46
00:02:54,103 --> 00:02:56,203
since Ji Hyuk's not feeling well right now,

47
00:02:57,203 --> 00:02:58,643
he's avoiding her,

48
00:02:59,673 --> 00:03:01,073
and Eun Oh is chasing after him.

49
00:03:04,673 --> 00:03:06,013
Poor Ji Hyuk.

50
00:03:09,213 --> 00:03:11,453
He's avoiding the very woman he likes.

51
00:03:17,293 --> 00:03:18,763
Seeing how it's taking a while,

52
00:03:19,993 --> 00:03:22,763
it must be hard for Ji Hyuk and unbearable for Eun Oh.

53
00:03:24,593 --> 00:03:26,063
Come on. I'll take you home.

54
00:03:26,933 --> 00:03:28,503
I was supposed to go with Ji Hyuk.

55
00:03:29,673 --> 00:03:31,473
Ji Hyuk texted me on his way out.

56
00:03:32,173 --> 00:03:33,873
He said he was running away from Eun Oh.

57
00:03:34,703 --> 00:03:36,273
He asked me to make sure you get home safe.

58
00:03:37,743 --> 00:03:40,813
If he was leaving early anyway, why did he come?

59
00:03:41,083 --> 00:03:42,183
He could've just stayed home.

60
00:03:43,253 --> 00:03:44,653
He came because he missed her, silly.

61
00:03:45,953 --> 00:03:47,683
He's all business at the office,

62
00:03:48,253 --> 00:03:50,453
so he doesn't give Eun Oh an inch.

63
00:03:51,553 --> 00:03:54,423
You think he's fine with that? You think he doesn't miss her?

64
00:03:55,763 --> 00:03:57,033
Using Gang Oh's invitation as an excuse,

65
00:03:58,133 --> 00:03:59,733
he just came to see her for an hour or two.

66
00:04:04,103 --> 00:04:06,943
But if you were coming, why did Ji Hyuk bring me along?

67
00:04:11,313 --> 00:04:13,943
I was against you two, but I give up.

68
00:04:15,083 --> 00:04:16,883
Now that I'm in this position myself,

69
00:04:17,253 --> 00:04:18,753
I've realized your own happiness is what's most important.

70
00:04:19,883 --> 00:04:23,493
How wonderful is it to have someone you're desperate to be with?

71
00:04:24,053 --> 00:04:25,263
Just think about yourselves.

72
00:04:27,563 --> 00:04:29,433
I guess he wanted to treat you to a nice meal.

73
00:04:30,193 --> 00:04:31,463
Because he trusts us.

74
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:36,203
Because he believes we've completely broken up?

75
00:04:40,373 --> 00:04:41,843
Because we have completely broken up.

76
00:04:44,613 --> 00:04:45,613
Right.

77
00:04:46,683 --> 00:04:48,453
There can't be an "us" anymore.

78
00:05:04,163 --> 00:05:05,403
I'll just take the bus.

79
00:05:06,233 --> 00:05:07,233
No.

80
00:05:07,763 --> 00:05:09,403
I promised Ji Hyuk...

81
00:05:10,273 --> 00:05:11,703
I'd make sure you get home safely.

82
00:05:13,273 --> 00:05:14,443
He's drawing a line.

83
00:05:14,943 --> 00:05:18,143
I hate that he's taking me home just because my brother asked.

84
00:05:37,963 --> 00:05:39,303
I have my own pockets, you know.

85
00:05:39,963 --> 00:05:41,773
Mine is warmer.

86
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:45,443
But then, your hand will get cold.

87
00:05:50,373 --> 00:05:52,783
Just until the taxi gets here. It's cold.

88
00:05:56,753 --> 00:05:57,753
Okay.

89
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:05,293
It's amazing how people can love each other enough to marry.

90
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:11,193
I feel so bad for Eun Oh and my brother.

91
00:06:25,783 --> 00:06:29,113
(Gang Oh)

92
00:06:32,883 --> 00:06:33,883
Eun Oh.

93
00:06:36,223 --> 00:06:37,293
Look, what I have...

94
00:06:39,093 --> 00:06:40,763
isn't kidney failure.

95
00:06:43,493 --> 00:06:45,133
I'm a patient...

96
00:06:46,603 --> 00:06:47,633
who needs a heart transplant.

97
00:06:51,303 --> 00:06:52,343
So, Eun Oh.

98
00:06:54,373 --> 00:06:55,473
Please...

99
00:06:58,813 --> 00:06:59,813
let me go.

100
00:07:02,153 --> 00:07:03,183
I'm begging you.

101
00:07:07,323 --> 00:07:08,693
For the time I have left,

102
00:07:10,723 --> 00:07:11,753
at least as friends,

103
00:07:14,063 --> 00:07:15,993
can't you let me see you in peace?

104
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:20,333
If you did that,

105
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:23,003
I would be so grateful.

106
00:07:26,443 --> 00:07:27,943
How could this have happened?

107
00:07:28,443 --> 00:07:29,443
Ji Hyuk...

108
00:07:31,743 --> 00:07:33,483
Please, just tell me...

109
00:07:38,413 --> 00:07:39,923
I can't talk about that right now.

110
00:07:43,493 --> 00:07:44,493
Ji Eun Oh.

111
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:50,263
You're being cruel.

112
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:54,033
You're forcing me...

113
00:07:56,573 --> 00:07:57,573
Fine.

114
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:03,733
Eun Oh.

115
00:09:05,973 --> 00:09:06,973
Just leave me...

116
00:09:10,613 --> 00:09:11,673
alone.

117
00:09:26,323 --> 00:09:27,323
Please.

118
00:09:35,903 --> 00:09:36,903
I'm sorry.

119
00:10:30,823 --> 00:10:31,823
Just now...

120
00:10:33,193 --> 00:10:36,863
Did you say you need a heart transplant?

121
00:10:48,273 --> 00:10:49,543
What's happening to me?

122
00:11:09,163 --> 00:11:13,333
What's going on? You didn't answer calls or texts.

123
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:18,103
Did you close up the shop and come home because of me?

124
00:11:18,603 --> 00:11:21,473
Listen to this one. She has no idea what time it is.

125
00:11:21,973 --> 00:11:24,243
We just closed the restaurant and got home.

126
00:11:24,843 --> 00:11:28,383
Have you been with that CEO guy this whole time?

127
00:11:31,253 --> 00:11:33,253
No, that's not it.

128
00:11:33,953 --> 00:11:34,953
Eun Oh.

129
00:11:36,193 --> 00:11:37,353
Have you been crying?

130
00:11:41,163 --> 00:11:43,593
Mom, I'm going to head in.

131
00:11:47,363 --> 00:11:49,073
Hey, come here. Come on.

132
00:11:50,803 --> 00:11:53,603
What's wrong? What? What happened?

133
00:11:54,743 --> 00:11:57,913
Why did you run after his car like that?

134
00:11:58,673 --> 00:12:01,483
I could tell something was off back at the restaurant.

135
00:12:02,653 --> 00:12:05,553
Did that CEO have a change of heart?

136
00:12:05,853 --> 00:12:10,393
No, that can't be right. He was so devoted to you.

137
00:12:13,223 --> 00:12:15,593
Mom, can you just hold me?

138
00:12:16,563 --> 00:12:17,563
What?

139
00:12:18,093 --> 00:12:19,103
My gosh...

140
00:12:19,663 --> 00:12:22,203
What's gotten into you now?

141
00:12:26,873 --> 00:12:27,873
Mom.

142
00:12:28,973 --> 00:12:32,543
Ji Hyuk... He might be dying.

143
00:12:34,143 --> 00:12:35,983
He's dying.

144
00:12:37,413 --> 00:12:40,923
That's why he said I'm a burden to him.

145
00:12:42,353 --> 00:12:43,353
Oh, my...

146
00:12:46,023 --> 00:12:48,563
What are you talking about? Oh, sweetie.

147
00:12:50,063 --> 00:12:52,063
I'm so scared.

148
00:12:55,103 --> 00:12:58,173
Okay, first... Just calm down, Eun Oh.

149
00:12:58,233 --> 00:13:01,773
Eun Oh. My gosh, you're shaking so much.

150
00:13:02,313 --> 00:13:03,313
Calm down.

151
00:13:03,943 --> 00:13:05,413
Let's just calm down, okay?

152
00:13:06,483 --> 00:13:07,613
Calm down.

153
00:13:09,113 --> 00:13:10,513
Oh, dear.

154
00:13:36,213 --> 00:13:38,743
Goodbye, Park Jin Seok.

155
00:13:55,193 --> 00:13:56,333
It's over.

156
00:14:15,013 --> 00:14:16,853
Did she go to a friend's place for the night?

157
00:14:19,453 --> 00:14:21,583
But wait, she doesn't have any friends like that.

158
00:14:24,193 --> 00:14:25,193
No, that can't be it.

159
00:14:26,893 --> 00:14:29,133
I'm sure there's plenty I don't know about her.

160
00:14:54,753 --> 00:14:57,723
You're still coming in early, Ms. Ji Eun Oh.

161
00:15:01,793 --> 00:15:02,793
Yes.

162
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:05,733
I find I concentrate better in the morning.

163
00:15:06,933 --> 00:15:09,673
The 2nd draft for Living Life 30. I need it by today.

164
00:15:12,743 --> 00:15:13,903
Yes, understood.

165
00:15:15,243 --> 00:15:17,743
Good. It feels like a real office now.

166
00:15:26,453 --> 00:15:29,393
Is this really what you wanted?

167
00:15:46,943 --> 00:15:48,873
I actually slept through the night.

168
00:15:52,443 --> 00:15:55,313
Since there's no way I can resolve this on my own,

169
00:15:55,853 --> 00:15:58,213
I've come here to ask for your help.

170
00:16:01,083 --> 00:16:05,923
Twenty-six years ago, I remarried Park Jin Seok of the Shoe Joy Group.

171
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:09,993
I brought my four-year-old son with me into the marriage.

172
00:16:11,563 --> 00:16:13,033
Chairman Park Jin Seok, on the other hand,

173
00:16:13,503 --> 00:16:15,903
already had a seven-year-old son of his own,

174
00:16:16,773 --> 00:16:20,003
and together, we had a daughter.

175
00:16:20,703 --> 00:16:23,513
We lived a happy life for 26 years.

176
00:16:25,013 --> 00:16:26,943
He has some trauma from his past,

177
00:16:27,413 --> 00:16:30,283
and I knew he hated being deceived more than anything.

178
00:16:31,453 --> 00:16:32,983
But my husband, disappointed in me,

179
00:16:33,453 --> 00:16:35,253
concluded that I had been deceiving him...

180
00:16:35,793 --> 00:16:37,193
for our entire 26 years together.

181
00:16:38,293 --> 00:16:39,323
And then, one day,

182
00:16:40,423 --> 00:16:43,533
out of the blue, he told me to get out of the house.

183
00:16:44,363 --> 00:16:46,033
When I tried to talk things over,

184
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:49,573
he dragged me barefoot out the front gate and threw me out.

185
00:16:51,533 --> 00:16:54,173
I had no idea any of this was coming.

186
00:16:55,173 --> 00:16:56,413
But Chairman Park Jin Seok...

187
00:16:57,013 --> 00:17:01,343
had already placed liens on all of my real estate.

188
00:17:01,813 --> 00:17:03,353
He'd hidden everything I owned, including...

189
00:17:03,683 --> 00:17:06,853
all my jewelry, cash, and foreign currency.

190
00:17:07,853 --> 00:17:10,723
He even took my credit cards...

191
00:17:11,453 --> 00:17:14,863
and cleaned out my bank accounts.

192
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:19,233
He left me with only 2,000 dollars on my debit card...

193
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:21,963
and kicked me to the curb.

194
00:17:24,903 --> 00:17:26,603
At first, I just thought...

195
00:17:26,903 --> 00:17:29,843
- Is this for real? Is it AI? - This is insane. Shoe Joy is toast.

196
00:17:29,913 --> 00:17:31,213
He kicked her out with just 2,000 dollars?

197
00:17:31,273 --> 00:17:33,783
"Deceived for 26 years?" As if. Ma'am, you need police protection.

198
00:17:33,843 --> 00:17:35,243
See? The super-rich are always so messed up.

199
00:17:35,313 --> 00:17:37,183
Being dragged out barefoot is chilling.

200
00:17:37,253 --> 00:17:39,753
After 26 years together? How could he do something like that?

201
00:17:39,823 --> 00:17:43,823
Even if she lied, it's still abuse. The liens, hiding all her assets...

202
00:17:43,893 --> 00:17:46,463
- That's grounds for prison. - Shoe Joy Group's image is ruined.

203
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:49,263
The liens are the final nail in the coffin. Poor woman.

204
00:17:50,993 --> 00:17:52,703
- That's right. - He refuses to grant me a divorce.

205
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:55,003
I'm the victim here.

206
00:17:56,073 --> 00:17:58,473
My husband of 26 years, and the father of our daughter...

207
00:17:59,103 --> 00:18:03,443
I did everything I could to keep him from being publicly shamed.

208
00:18:07,743 --> 00:18:08,743
Hello?

209
00:18:09,253 --> 00:18:10,913
(Vice President Park Seong Jae)

210
00:18:11,183 --> 00:18:13,123
What's this about a weird interview circulating on YouTube?

211
00:18:15,083 --> 00:18:16,093
And then, one day,

212
00:18:17,323 --> 00:18:20,293
out of the blue, he told me to get out of the house.

213
00:18:20,363 --> 00:18:21,663
(Vice President Park Seong Jae)

214
00:18:21,723 --> 00:18:23,293
When I tried to talk things over,

215
00:18:24,463 --> 00:18:27,563
he dragged me barefoot out the front gate and threw me out.

216
00:18:32,943 --> 00:18:33,943
Honey.

217
00:18:34,373 --> 00:18:38,373
If you don't really intend to leave me homeless on the street,

218
00:18:39,143 --> 00:18:40,443
then either grant me a divorce...

219
00:18:41,583 --> 00:18:44,713
or at least give me back my assets.

220
00:18:45,713 --> 00:18:48,923
I never gave you permission to put a lien on my properties,

221
00:18:49,823 --> 00:18:52,393
and I never authorized you to use my official seal.

222
00:18:55,063 --> 00:18:56,093
And...

223
00:18:57,193 --> 00:18:58,193
I'm sorry...

224
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:00,433
that it's come to this.

225
00:19:05,703 --> 00:19:07,043
I didn't see this coming.

226
00:19:08,073 --> 00:19:09,313
I never would have expected this.

227
00:19:14,983 --> 00:19:15,983
Father.

228
00:19:16,783 --> 00:19:20,123
Did you illegally put liens on her properties?

229
00:19:21,323 --> 00:19:23,123
Why would you do something so reckless?

230
00:19:27,693 --> 00:19:31,193
Sir, the phones are ringing with calls from the media.

231
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:33,933
And our stock price has plummeted by nine percent.

232
00:19:37,303 --> 00:19:38,303
Get the legal team in here.

233
00:19:39,473 --> 00:19:42,543
And do what? There's no way out of this, Father!

234
00:19:43,373 --> 00:19:45,443
The truth will come out the second she files to cancel.

235
00:19:45,513 --> 00:19:47,643
Why make such a predictable move? It's not like you.

236
00:19:49,953 --> 00:19:53,323
Does she seem like the type to just let you take her assets?

237
00:19:54,183 --> 00:19:55,683
Especially when this all started over money?

238
00:19:56,723 --> 00:19:58,923
What did you think would happen if you took everything from her?

239
00:20:00,623 --> 00:20:01,693
I didn't take anything.

240
00:20:03,293 --> 00:20:04,333
What?

241
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:05,363
Hey, I'm back.

242
00:20:07,563 --> 00:20:09,163
Slacking off watching YouTube?

243
00:20:10,573 --> 00:20:12,943
How did you get out of there?

244
00:20:14,143 --> 00:20:15,143
Why?

245
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:18,243
Your family's in huge trouble.

246
00:20:18,943 --> 00:20:19,983
(The Wife's Shocking Confession!)

247
00:20:19,983 --> 00:20:22,953
My son was always an outsider in the Park family.

248
00:20:23,883 --> 00:20:26,923
He was dying, after a miserable life on eggshells.

249
00:20:30,323 --> 00:20:32,353
But I couldn't bring myself to tell my husband.

250
00:20:33,893 --> 00:20:35,563
I was afraid I'd be a bother.

251
00:20:36,593 --> 00:20:38,533
How could my mom do this?

252
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:41,233
How could she go public with this?

253
00:20:44,103 --> 00:20:47,103
Shoe Joy's stock is plummeting.

254
00:20:49,573 --> 00:20:50,573
She attacked the company...

255
00:20:51,813 --> 00:20:53,613
and our family.

256
00:20:56,053 --> 00:20:59,623
So she doesn't care what happens to Dad, my brother, or me?

257
00:21:01,723 --> 00:21:03,623
That's ruthless.

258
00:21:05,593 --> 00:21:08,523
But why would the Chairman go to such extremes?

259
00:21:10,863 --> 00:21:12,563
Because to my mom, money is everything.

260
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:16,203
He must've wanted to punish her by hitting her where it hurts.

261
00:21:18,573 --> 00:21:22,943
It seems the Chairman really underestimated your mother.

262
00:21:24,013 --> 00:21:26,383
(Shoe Joy Family Feud Escalates, Hidden Asset Allegations Grow)

263
00:21:28,943 --> 00:21:31,983
(Shoe Joy Chairman's Wife's Expose: Park Jin Seok Against His Wife...)

264
00:21:36,723 --> 00:21:38,223
