Didn't you see that part?

519
00:40:20,813 --> 00:40:21,913
I saw that part, too.

520
00:40:24,353 --> 00:40:26,513
Then why are you here?

521
00:40:28,553 --> 00:40:30,023
I couldn't just stay away.

522
00:40:31,653 --> 00:40:33,253
Because I knew you'd be all alone.

523
00:40:34,223 --> 00:40:37,263
You can't vent to my older brother since he's sick,

524
00:40:38,493 --> 00:40:40,393
so I figured you were just enduring it all by yourself.

525
00:40:41,003 --> 00:40:42,533
I came because I wanted to be here for you.

526
00:40:49,303 --> 00:40:50,303
You're...

527
00:40:51,343 --> 00:40:52,843
always so unpredictable.

528
00:40:56,183 --> 00:40:57,183
Hey.

529
00:40:57,883 --> 00:40:59,083
It's been really hard on you, hasn't it?

530
00:41:01,653 --> 00:41:02,853
It's all over now.

531
00:41:03,753 --> 00:41:05,253
No, I mean all this time.

532
00:41:06,423 --> 00:41:08,563
Ever since your mom left, up until now.

533
00:41:09,193 --> 00:41:10,633
How hard must it have been for you?

534
00:41:11,263 --> 00:41:12,793
How lonely must you have been?

535
00:41:15,863 --> 00:41:17,903
You could have vented to me when we saw each other.

536
00:41:19,833 --> 00:41:21,803
You should've told me how lonely you were...

537
00:41:21,803 --> 00:41:23,073
because of that awful stepmom.

538
00:41:26,613 --> 00:41:27,613
That's all in the past.

539
00:41:28,043 --> 00:41:29,783
If I'd known who she really was,

540
00:41:29,783 --> 00:41:31,583
I wouldn't have held back when she came to see me.

541
00:41:33,113 --> 00:41:34,123
She came to see you?

542
00:41:35,553 --> 00:41:36,553
That woman...

543
00:41:37,323 --> 00:41:38,593
came to see you?

544
00:41:39,693 --> 00:41:40,693
What?

545
00:41:41,293 --> 00:41:42,293
Did she?

546
00:41:44,163 --> 00:41:45,163
Yes.

547
00:41:46,663 --> 00:41:48,603
So that's why my dad called you in?

548
00:41:51,873 --> 00:41:53,973
Why wouldn't you tell me something like that?

549
00:41:54,273 --> 00:41:57,313
For the same reason you didn't tell me.

550
00:41:58,113 --> 00:41:59,843
I knew you'd be upset if I told you.

551
00:42:10,423 --> 00:42:11,723
It's all in the past now anyway.

552
00:42:12,923 --> 00:42:14,263
I appreciate you thinking of me.

553
00:42:14,963 --> 00:42:15,963
But...

554
00:42:17,123 --> 00:42:18,163
Don't do this again.

555
00:42:19,563 --> 00:42:20,863
And you won't have to.

556
00:42:25,003 --> 00:42:26,703
But you're struggling right now.

557
00:42:29,303 --> 00:42:30,443
I can handle it.

558
00:42:33,343 --> 00:42:34,343
Still...

559
00:42:35,843 --> 00:42:37,753
I just wanted to give you a hug.

560
00:42:54,833 --> 00:42:55,833
Hey.

561
00:43:12,413 --> 00:43:13,653
Your hands are so cold.

562
00:43:18,053 --> 00:43:19,153
All this time...

563
00:43:20,293 --> 00:43:21,723
You've been through so much.

564
00:43:24,233 --> 00:43:26,593
I don't know how you grew up with someone like that...

565
00:43:27,463 --> 00:43:29,363
and still turned out to be such a wonderful person.

566
00:43:31,873 --> 00:43:32,873
And...

567
00:43:35,873 --> 00:43:36,873
Thank you.

568
00:43:40,313 --> 00:43:44,183
For being there for my older brother.

569
00:43:44,783 --> 00:43:45,913
It means so much to me.

570
00:43:56,163 --> 00:43:58,963
You're going to meet someone amazing one day.

571
00:44:01,603 --> 00:44:02,903
I'll pray that you do.

572
00:44:06,533 --> 00:44:07,543
And...

573
00:44:10,973 --> 00:44:13,613
from now on, I'm your best friend's sister.

574
00:44:16,283 --> 00:44:18,613
If anything's bothering you, tell me all about it.

575
00:44:21,083 --> 00:44:22,553
I'll be here to listen.

576
00:44:33,593 --> 00:44:34,603
I should get going.

577
00:45:51,013 --> 00:45:53,943
- So, has Ji Wan gone downstairs? - Yes.

578
00:45:54,383 --> 00:45:56,543
He usually goes right to his room,

579
00:45:56,813 --> 00:45:59,683
but he stuck around to gossip about the big news today.

580
00:46:00,513 --> 00:46:01,523
What about Su Bin?

581
00:46:03,423 --> 00:46:04,653
She's not home yet.

582
00:46:07,523 --> 00:46:09,963
Hey, honey.

583
00:46:11,333 --> 00:46:13,093
About Su Bin and Seong Jae...

584
00:46:13,863 --> 00:46:15,633
What do you think about letting them date?

585
00:46:16,763 --> 00:46:17,773
You think so, too?

586
00:46:18,633 --> 00:46:20,303
I was thinking the exact same thing.

587
00:46:20,973 --> 00:46:24,843
I keep worrying about Seong Jae, and watching Su Bin hide her pain...

588
00:46:25,473 --> 00:46:27,073
is just unbearable.

589
00:46:28,043 --> 00:46:30,313
Well, you never know what the future holds,

590
00:46:31,453 --> 00:46:33,853
and their happiness is what's most important.

591
00:46:38,523 --> 00:46:40,623
- I'm home. - You're back.

592
00:46:41,023 --> 00:46:42,563
You were just with Seong Jae, weren't you?

593
00:46:43,123 --> 00:46:45,763
I'm sorry. I just went to comfort him.

594
00:46:46,593 --> 00:46:47,703
You did the right thing.

595
00:46:49,163 --> 00:46:50,163
I did?

596
00:46:51,333 --> 00:46:52,433
Why don't you just keep seeing him?

597
00:46:54,173 --> 00:46:55,243
Mom.

598
00:46:56,403 --> 00:46:58,513
I just can't stand to see you like this anymore.

599
00:47:00,313 --> 00:47:03,043
You think I'm fooled just because you're smiling on the outside?

600
00:47:04,013 --> 00:47:05,713
I'm your mother, for goodness' sake.

601
00:47:06,013 --> 00:47:09,223
I know if you're crying or laughing just from the back of your head.

602
00:47:10,623 --> 00:47:13,423
No, Mom. With you and Dad already so upset,

603
00:47:13,623 --> 00:47:14,963
you don't have to give me your blessing.

604
00:47:16,623 --> 00:47:18,433
Not with everything going on with Ji Hyuk.

605
00:47:19,393 --> 00:47:21,963
Today was just a slip-up.

606
00:47:24,503 --> 00:47:25,703
Date him while you have our blessing.

607
00:47:26,273 --> 00:47:27,873
It's just dating. We're telling you to give it a try.

608
00:47:30,673 --> 00:47:31,673
Thank you.

609
00:47:35,643 --> 00:47:36,643
Honestly.

610
00:47:36,943 --> 00:47:38,983
You can never win with your kids, can you?

611
00:47:42,183 --> 00:47:45,253
Ji Hyuk, what brings you down? Do you need something?

612
00:47:45,453 --> 00:47:47,823
I just had to use the bathroom.

613
00:47:48,523 --> 00:47:50,323
Didn't you just go a little while ago?

614
00:47:51,193 --> 00:47:52,663
Did you drink a lot of water today?

615
00:47:54,133 --> 00:47:57,433
I guess so. Mom, here, let me get that.

616
00:47:59,933 --> 00:48:02,643
People go more often in the winter. What's the big deal?

617
00:48:09,013 --> 00:48:13,183
I think we should have Ji Hyuk move into my mother's old room.

618
00:48:14,213 --> 00:48:15,223
Ji Hyuk?

619
00:48:16,123 --> 00:48:18,353
But Ji Wan is supposed to move into that room.

620
00:48:18,793 --> 00:48:21,893
We can just have Ji Wan move into Ji Hyuk's room upstairs.

621
00:48:22,523 --> 00:48:26,793
It was his room. He gave it up when my parents moved in.

622
00:48:27,463 --> 00:48:29,233
Honey, that was ages ago.

623
00:48:29,533 --> 00:48:30,603
He was a high school freshman, wasn't he?

624
00:48:30,973 --> 00:48:33,173
What difference does it make when it was?

625
00:48:34,003 --> 00:48:37,743
I still feel bad we made him leave the room he put so much work into.

626
00:48:38,413 --> 00:48:40,213
I'm sure that's what my mother would have wanted.

627
00:48:41,183 --> 00:48:44,853
Why move two people around? Ji Wan just needs to move upstairs.

628
00:48:44,913 --> 00:48:47,953
Are you not listening to me? It was originally his room,

629
00:48:48,123 --> 00:48:49,553
so I'm saying we should give it back to him.

630
00:48:50,153 --> 00:48:52,653
But isn't Ji Hyuk leaving home soon anyway?

631
00:48:52,723 --> 00:48:55,663
- And how would you know that? - Why are you getting so angry?

632
00:48:56,023 --> 00:48:57,023
That's strange.

633
00:48:58,833 --> 00:49:02,003
- Hey, why are you two fighting? - We're not. It's nothing serious.

634
00:49:03,133 --> 00:49:04,233
Listen, Ji Hyuk.

635
00:49:04,903 --> 00:49:07,673
I was saying Ji Wan should move into your grandmother's old room,

636
00:49:07,943 --> 00:49:11,413
but your dad insists you have it, since it was yours to begin with.

637
00:49:12,673 --> 00:49:14,813
Actually... I'd love that.

638
00:49:16,483 --> 00:49:19,453
- You would? - Of course. It was my room first.

639
00:49:20,483 --> 00:49:24,993
It still reminds me of Grandma. Yes, I'll take it back.

640
00:49:30,363 --> 00:49:31,633
He's being weird, too.

641
00:49:32,263 --> 00:49:35,063
All he does here is sleep. Why insist on that room?

642
00:49:35,833 --> 00:49:37,933
It's on the first floor. He'll hear everyone moving around.

643
00:49:46,443 --> 00:49:50,083
Compared to your last visit, your echocardiogram results...

644
00:49:51,213 --> 00:49:53,213
show that your heart's contractility has worsened slightly.

645
00:49:56,023 --> 00:49:58,353
It seems your heart is getting progressively more fatigued,

646
00:49:58,653 --> 00:50:02,663
so we need to increase the dose of your oral diuretic.

647
00:50:05,693 --> 00:50:06,693
I see.

648
00:50:13,303 --> 00:50:14,303
Ji Hyuk!

649
00:50:15,573 --> 00:50:19,273
My meeting at Headquarters ended just as you were getting off work.

650
00:50:20,513 --> 00:50:22,743
What does my schedule have to do with anything?

651
00:50:23,843 --> 00:50:25,613
You and I...

652
00:50:26,353 --> 00:50:27,413
have somewhere to be.

653
00:50:28,623 --> 00:50:29,623
Where?

654
00:50:39,733 --> 00:50:41,103
This is so good.

655
00:50:41,703 --> 00:50:44,473
It's almost too pretty to eat, but it tastes even better.

656
00:50:46,273 --> 00:50:48,603
Apparently, this place is pretty famous.

657
00:50:49,073 --> 00:50:50,603
Ji Hyuk, have some.

658
00:50:53,313 --> 00:50:56,213
I'm not a big fan of sweets lately.

659
00:50:56,283 --> 00:50:58,783
It's no fun eating alone.

660
00:51:00,753 --> 00:51:01,883
I should take a picture.

661
00:51:04,123 --> 00:51:06,953
I'll post it in my group chat.

662
00:51:09,893 --> 00:51:11,133
I always hoped that when I made a lot of money,

663
00:51:12,463 --> 00:51:13,533
you could stop working.

664
00:51:14,503 --> 00:51:15,703
I would've sent you on trips...

665
00:51:16,333 --> 00:51:17,333
That was my dream.

666
00:51:17,973 --> 00:51:18,973
There you go again.

667
00:51:19,603 --> 00:51:22,603
The other day at the shop, you looked at me with such pity.

668
00:51:23,243 --> 00:51:24,913
It really upset me.

669
00:51:25,573 --> 00:51:26,573
No, that's not...

670
00:51:27,143 --> 00:51:28,613
I wasn't pitying you.

671
00:51:29,913 --> 00:51:32,453
Mom, did it really upset you?

672
00:51:32,883 --> 00:51:34,413
We've talked about this before.

673
00:51:35,053 --> 00:51:38,753
Kids these days aren't expected to support their aging parents.

674
00:51:39,293 --> 00:51:43,763
I work hard to take care of myself and not rely on my children.

675
00:51:44,263 --> 00:51:46,493
You have no right to pity me.

676
00:51:50,333 --> 00:51:51,333
I'm sorry, Mom.

677
00:51:53,303 --> 00:51:55,003
No, it's just that when I see you working,

678
00:51:55,673 --> 00:51:57,203
I guess it just gets to me.

679
00:51:57,873 --> 00:51:59,573
Even this, you looking out for me... It makes me uncomfortable.

680
00:52:00,773 --> 00:52:04,653
I was always busy with you kids, your grandparents, and housework.

681
00:52:05,313 --> 00:52:09,453
So there's a lot I never got to do, but I never had any regrets.

682
00:52:10,023 --> 00:52:12,423
Because that's just life. You live with the hand you're dealt.

683
00:52:13,493 --> 00:52:16,123
But when you try hard to make up for all the things I missed out on,

684
00:52:16,463 --> 00:52:18,293
it makes me feel like some pitiful person.

685
00:52:21,263 --> 00:52:24,773
I never meant to make you feel that way, Mom.

686
00:52:26,773 --> 00:52:29,743
I guess it's because this is so out of character for me.

687
00:52:30,503 --> 00:52:31,513
That's it.

688
00:52:32,313 --> 00:52:34,113
So that's why I was feeling that way.

689
00:52:34,983 --> 00:52:37,283
That's why they say if someone acts out of character,

690
00:52:37,343 --> 00:52:39,083
it means their time is almost up.

691
00:52:40,253 --> 00:52:41,523
Honestly.

692
00:52:44,553 --> 00:52:45,553
I guess you're right.

693
00:52:48,423 --> 00:52:49,863
I should've been doing this all along.

694
00:52:50,993 --> 00:52:53,293
But it's not like it's a bad thing.

695
00:52:56,463 --> 00:52:57,463
This is so delicious.

696
00:52:58,573 --> 00:52:59,573
I'm glad you're enjoying it.

697
00:53:01,573 --> 00:53:03,173
I guess I'm really lucky.

698
00:53:04,973 --> 00:53:07,613
I don't have to worry about taking care of you and Dad later.

699
00:53:08,683 --> 00:53:09,683
If I die,

700
00:53:11,653 --> 00:53:13,013
I won't be able to do it anyway.

701
00:53:14,553 --> 00:53:15,553
That's right.

702
00:53:16,323 --> 00:53:18,653
Don't you worry about us. Just focus on your company.

703
00:53:19,823 --> 00:53:20,823
For me,

704
00:53:21,663 --> 00:53:24,793
when I present our products and hear from customers that they're working,

705
00:53:25,093 --> 00:53:26,333
it's so rewarding, and it makes me proud.

706
00:53:26,893 --> 00:53:28,363
I can only imagine how you must feel.

707
00:53:30,963 --> 00:53:32,533
If you grow your company into something great,

708
00:53:32,903 --> 00:53:36,303
just seeing you succeed is the best for your father and me.

709
00:53:39,573 --> 00:53:40,573
Yes.

710
00:53:41,283 --> 00:53:43,113
Ji Hyuk, what do you feel like eating?

711
00:53:43,843 --> 00:53:45,953
It's been a while, so I'll make you a proper home-cooked meal.

712
00:53:48,223 --> 00:53:49,223
Mushroom hot pot?

713
00:53:50,453 --> 00:53:53,753
I'll make it lightly seasoned, so don't worry and come on over.

714
00:53:54,253 --> 00:53:56,563
And you can just skip the broth.

715
00:54:00,363 --> 00:54:03,203
- Dad, I'm here. I'm heading up now. - What?

716
00:54:03,263 --> 00:54:04,263
What's that smell?

717
00:54:05,073 --> 00:54:07,303
Wait, you two came in together?

718
00:54:07,603 --> 00:54:09,243
Ji Hyuk and I were on a little date.

719
00:54:09,903 --> 00:54:11,773
Honey, have you ever been to a dessert cafe?

720
00:54:15,283 --> 00:54:16,283
What?

721
00:54:20,713 --> 00:54:21,923
You're making mushroom hot pot.

722
00:54:22,683 --> 00:54:23,983
Did Ji Hyuk tell you in advance?

723
00:54:24,083 --> 00:54:26,753
No. I saw a recipe on YouTube and decided to try it.

724
00:54:26,993 --> 00:54:30,023
Wow. Aren't you getting too good at cooking?

725
00:54:33,463 --> 00:54:34,463
What?

726
00:54:35,363 --> 00:54:36,503
It's completely bland.

727
00:54:41,303 --> 00:54:42,643
- Hey! - My gosh!

728
00:54:44,173 --> 00:54:45,173
Honey!

729
00:54:47,413 --> 00:54:49,083
Get out of the way.

730
00:54:49,683 --> 00:54:51,713
I'll clean this up, so just go on. Hurry.

731
00:54:52,013 --> 00:54:55,253
Gosh, what's gotten into you?

732
00:54:56,023 --> 00:54:57,353
Oh, man...

733
00:54:58,253 --> 00:55:02,623
I'm the one cooking. Why are you dumping salt in there?

734
00:55:03,063 --> 00:55:04,763
Everyone has different tastes these days,

735
00:55:05,033 --> 00:55:08,803
and I don't like salty food lately, so I made it bland on purpose.

736
00:55:09,503 --> 00:55:11,063
But it tasted like plain water.

737
00:55:12,373 --> 00:55:16,073
No, the plan was to let everyone season their own bowl later.

738
00:55:16,473 --> 00:55:18,473
It's up to the chef. What's the big deal?

739
00:55:19,613 --> 00:55:21,173
Excuse me, Chef.

740
00:55:21,913 --> 00:55:23,143
Just call me when it's ready.

741
00:55:28,823 --> 00:55:29,823
Lee Sang Cheol.

742
00:55:30,823 --> 00:55:31,953
Get a grip.

743
00:55:32,423 --> 00:55:34,293
Why are you getting so worked up over nothing?

744
00:55:51,073 --> 00:55:52,073
Oh, boy.

745
00:56:10,393 --> 00:56:11,863
You should just ask her to come back.

746
00:56:14,163 --> 00:56:15,533
This house feels so empty,

747
00:56:16,633 --> 00:56:18,433
and you're drinking at home when you never used to.

748
00:56:20,273 --> 00:56:22,073
Truth is, by taking out the mortgage and leaving her with nothing...

749
00:56:23,473 --> 00:56:24,643
Isn't it that you can't let her go, Dad?

750
00:56:27,173 --> 00:56:29,283
I'm not miserable because she's gone.

751
00:56:29,883 --> 00:56:32,183
But you've just created a reason to stay entangled with her.

752
00:56:33,153 --> 00:56:34,153
If it were me,

753
00:56:35,123 --> 00:56:36,123
I'd get a divorce.

754
00:56:37,983 --> 00:56:42,363
I'm angry at my own foolishness that doesn't fade with time.

755
00:56:44,723 --> 00:56:47,293
It's because I'm still so angry with myself,

756
00:56:48,433 --> 00:56:49,433
so just leave me alone.

757
00:57:21,633 --> 00:57:23,933
You should wear one with a bigger rock.

758
00:57:24,633 --> 00:57:27,803
But this is the engagement ring you gave me when you proposed,

759
00:57:28,103 --> 00:57:29,973
so I love it the most.

760
00:57:55,163 --> 00:57:57,303
Less than 10,000 dollars for a 1-carat?

761
00:57:57,933 --> 00:58:01,203
You said it's 26 years old, right? And you don't have the certificate.

762
00:58:01,303 --> 00:58:03,003
I can't offer more than 5,000 dollars.

763
00:58:03,073 --> 00:58:05,243
(Diamond)

764
00:58:23,763 --> 00:58:25,133
We'll get going.

765
00:58:25,333 --> 00:58:28,163
- Okay, take care. - Good work.

766
00:58:54,193 --> 00:58:57,223
- Ji Eun Oh. - I'm here to get something.

767
00:58:57,863 --> 00:59:00,493
Something you were meant to give me, but you never did.

768
00:59:03,663 --> 00:59:04,663
And what's that?

769
00:59:05,473 --> 00:59:06,473
Our memories.

770
00:59:08,203 --> 00:59:09,473
The memories of you and me...

771
00:59:10,803 --> 00:59:13,673
I need the memory of us liking each other.

772
00:59:15,713 --> 00:59:16,713
What?

773
00:59:17,013 --> 00:59:18,483
I've been thinking, and...

774
00:59:21,013 --> 00:59:22,083
if I let you...

775
00:59:23,053 --> 00:59:25,323
just go on your own, all lonely like this,

776
00:59:26,593 --> 00:59:28,253
I think I'll regret it for the rest of my life.

777
00:59:29,793 --> 00:59:31,593
I might never be able to be with anyone else.

778
00:59:35,233 --> 00:59:36,533
That's ridiculous.

779
00:59:39,273 --> 00:59:41,533
- Get out. - Doesn't this feel unfair, Ji Hyuk?

780
00:59:42,673 --> 00:59:44,043
Because I think it's incredibly unfair.

781
00:59:44,573 --> 00:59:48,483
After all we've been through... I liked you first, then you did.

782
00:59:49,283 --> 00:59:51,483
And now that I finally have feelings for you again,

783
00:59:52,513 --> 00:59:54,313
you want us to just drift apart again?

784
00:59:55,653 --> 00:59:56,683
I refuse.

785
01:00:01,763 --> 01:00:03,263
Why would you date a dying man?

786
01:00:04,163 --> 01:00:05,533
Why would you want that kind of relationship?

787
01:00:07,533 --> 01:00:08,733
A relationship with no future.

788
01:00:11,903 --> 01:00:13,733
(AP Group, Younglim)

789
01:00:13,803 --> 01:00:14,903
Because it's hard on me.

790
01:00:15,773 --> 01:00:18,573
This is killing me. Do you hear me? It's killing me.

791
01:00:24,783 --> 01:00:25,783
Ji Eun Oh.

792
01:00:27,353 --> 01:00:28,483
You and I...

793
01:00:28,983 --> 01:00:30,483
have been through everything together.

794
01:00:31,583 --> 01:00:33,323
Things are already complicated between us.

795
01:00:34,023 --> 01:00:35,323
If you add love on top of all that,

796
01:00:36,463 --> 01:00:38,063
do you really think you'll be able to forget me easily?

797
01:00:39,893 --> 01:00:41,863
This isn't a normal relationship where we can just break up.

798
01:00:42,633 --> 01:00:44,303
You deserve to meet someone great, don't you?

799
01:00:46,673 --> 01:00:48,903
You think you're really something, don't you?

800
01:00:50,243 --> 01:00:53,073
You think I'll spend my whole life pining for you?

801
01:01:00,413 --> 01:01:01,413
You...

802
01:01:04,353 --> 01:01:05,553
You pity me.

803
01:01:14,193 --> 01:01:15,403
Don't pity me.

804
01:01:16,933 --> 01:01:18,003
On my own,

805
01:01:19,033 --> 01:01:20,373
I can live a good life until I'm gone.

806
01:01:22,443 --> 01:01:23,503
So just stop.

807
01:01:31,483 --> 01:01:33,353
Do you really think I'm doing this because I feel so sorry for you...

808
01:01:34,453 --> 01:01:37,883
that I want to stay with you until the very end out of pity?

809
01:01:39,453 --> 01:01:40,453
No.

810
01:01:42,293 --> 01:01:43,863
I'm really doing this for myself.

811
01:01:46,493 --> 01:01:48,633
You can't have regrets if you leave nothing undone.

812
01:01:50,803 --> 01:01:52,133
"I did everything I could."

813
01:01:53,233 --> 01:01:54,333
"I did enough."

814
01:01:55,103 --> 01:01:56,473
"I tried every last thing."

815
01:01:57,643 --> 01:01:59,073
That's just who I am.

816
01:02:00,473 --> 01:02:01,813
Do you really not know me by now?

817
01:02:05,583 --> 01:02:06,653
I don't care.

818
01:02:12,523 --> 01:02:14,353
For you, it'll all be over when you're gone,

819
01:02:17,393 --> 01:02:19,133
but I'm the one who has to keep on living.

820
01:02:23,503 --> 01:02:25,303
So whose feelings matter more here?

821
01:02:27,173 --> 01:02:29,003
Mine, right?

822
01:02:31,473 --> 01:02:33,243
I'm the one who's going to suffer more.

823
01:02:49,023 --> 01:02:50,023
So...

824
01:02:53,493 --> 01:02:55,133
let me do this...

825
01:02:57,063 --> 01:02:58,203
my way.

826
01:03:00,903 --> 01:03:01,903
Eun Oh.

827
01:03:04,973 --> 01:03:06,243
I want to live a peaceful,

828
01:03:07,943 --> 01:03:09,513
ordinary life until the end.

829
01:03:13,313 --> 01:03:14,783
In that ordinary life,

830
01:03:16,523 --> 01:03:17,523
please let me be a part of it.

831
01:03:19,793 --> 01:03:20,793
I also...

832
01:03:22,663 --> 01:03:24,163
want to be the most important person...

833
01:03:25,363 --> 01:03:27,693
in your everyday life.

834
01:03:30,533 --> 01:03:31,703
A memory like that...

835
01:03:33,203 --> 01:03:34,333
I need it so badly.

836
01:03:46,313 --> 01:03:47,983
Why are you making this so hard on me?

837
01:03:53,253 --> 01:03:55,193
If you truly care about me,

838
01:03:58,963 --> 01:04:00,333
even if it's just for one day,

839
01:04:02,763 --> 01:04:04,703
please be my boyfriend.

840
01:04:14,973 --> 01:04:16,043
You can't regret this.

841
01:04:37,103 --> 01:04:38,333
And no taking it back.

842
01:06:47,163 --> 01:06:50,203
(Our Golden Days)

843
01:06:50,433 --> 01:06:54,003
I heard Ji Hyuk and Eun Oh decided to start dating.

844
01:06:54,003 --> 01:06:56,473
Do you really need a reason to like someone? You just do.

845
01:06:56,543 --> 01:06:59,043
Today, I'm here as your girlfriend.

846
01:06:59,343 --> 01:07:03,213
- Ko Seong Hui stole so many years. - Then just divorce her.

847
01:07:03,313 --> 01:07:06,353
She's at my studio. What am I supposed to do?

848
01:07:07,013 --> 01:07:09,623
You're my daughter. I am your mother.

849
01:07:09,823 --> 01:07:13,693
You know nothing about my life. How dare you lecture your mother?

850
01:07:13,853 --> 01:07:16,293
Woo Jin, you're all I have.

851
01:07:16,363 --> 01:07:19,133
Does Ji Hyuk need a heart transplant?

852
01:07:19,863 --> 01:07:21,133
I can't go on!

853
01:07:22,263 --> 01:07:25,473
What am I going to do? My poor Ji Hyuk.
